docs.abstract: Despite a reputation for being bound by tradition, companies are embracing changes that have modernized other workplaces.
docs.snippet: Despite a reputation for being bound by tradition, companies are embracing changes that have modernized other workplaces.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Abrams Books recently moved to new offices in Lower Manhattan from its longtime home in Chelsea, it hired the consultants that companies typically call in for their expertise in audiovisual, lighting, temperature and ventilation needs.

headline.main: Book Publishers Adopt a New Office Image: Openness

docs.abstract: It was the firm’s most notable victory in its fight with Jay Alix, who has accused McKinsey of repeatedly defrauding the bankruptcy courts.
docs.snippet: It was the firm’s most notable victory in its fight with Jay Alix, who has accused McKinsey of repeatedly defrauding the bankruptcy courts.
docs.lead_paragraph: A federal judge dismissed a lawsuit that accused the consulting firm McKinsey & Company of intentionally filing false statements in several bankruptcy courts to win lucrative contracts to work on big corporate restructurings.

headline.main: Racketeering Lawsuit Against McKinsey Is Dismissed

docs.abstract: An oversight board proposed a way to deal with the island’s debt crisis, which took an act of Congress and lots of wrangling.
docs.snippet: An oversight board proposed a way to deal with the island’s debt crisis, which took an act of Congress and lots of wrangling.
docs.lead_paragraph: After years of wrangling with its creditors, Puerto Rico disclosed a plan Friday for resolving the biggest governmental bankruptcy in United States history, by cutting $129 billion in debts to about $86 billion — a reduction of 33 percent.

headline.main: $129 Billion Puerto Rico Bankruptcy Plan Could Be Model for States
headline.print_headline: Puerto Rico’s Solvency Plan Trims Its Debt by a Third

docs.abstract: The pace may allow the electric-car maker to fulfill its forecast for the year. But analysts are skeptical that sales are enough to yield a profit.
docs.snippet: The pace may allow the electric-car maker to fulfill its forecast for the year. But analysts are skeptical that sales are enough to yield a profit.
docs.lead_paragraph: Tesla reported record quarterly deliveries on Wednesday, putting the electric-car maker within reach of its goal for the year. But analysts remain skeptical that the company will show a profit for the period.

headline.main: Tesla’s Record Deliveries Aren’t Enough for Investors
headline.print_headline: Tesla Deliveries Climb To a Quarterly Record, But Challenges Remain

docs.abstract: A guilty plea and the recession dented Mr. Epstein’s wealth and reputation in 2008. But the financier bounced back in a big way in the Virgin Islands.
docs.snippet: A guilty plea and the recession dented Mr. Epstein’s wealth and reputation in 2008. But the financier bounced back in a big way in the Virgin Islands.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jeffrey Epstein’s biggest client had deserted him, his money management firm had lost more than $150 million during the financial crisis, and he was a registered sex offender. But after he started a new company with a wildly speculative business plan in 2012, Mr. Epstein had no problem pulling in cash.

headline.main: Jeffrey Epstein Raked In $200 Million After Legal and Financial Crises
headline.print_headline: After Plea Deal, Epstein Made $200 Million

byline.original: By Matthew Goldstein and Steve Eder

docs.abstract: As rising temperatures drastically reshape Iceland’s landscape, businesses and the government are spending millions for survival and profit.
docs.snippet: As rising temperatures drastically reshape Iceland’s landscape, businesses and the government are spending millions for survival and profit.
docs.lead_paragraph: HÖFN, Iceland — From the offices of the fishing operation founded by his family two generations ago, Adalsteinn Ingólfsson has watched the massive Vatnajökull glacier shrink year after year. Rising temperatures have already winnowed the types of fish he can catch. But the wilting ice mass, Iceland’s largest, is a strange new challenge to business.

headline.main: What Worries Iceland? A World Without Ice. It Is Preparing.
headline.print_headline: A World Without Ice? Iceland Is Preparing
